  "texts": [
    "Understanding artificial intelligenceBefore delving into the intersection of AI with the legal realm, it is crucial to first establish a clear understanding of what AI encompasses.",
    "While AI significantly influences various aspects of contemporary life, the expectation for a universally agreed-upon definition is not straightforward.",
    "This is due to AI's relative novelty and its evolving nature, which means its widespread adoption and understanding are still developing.",
    "Moreover, the absence of a cohesive international legal framework and the variability in legal definitions and regulations across different countries make the pursuit of a universal definition challenging in the current global landscape [10].At its essence, AI can be succinctly characterised as a technological innovation designed to automate processes and tasks that have historically necessitated human cognitive abilities [11].",
    "This broad category encompasses a range of computational techniques designed to augment machine functionality in complex cognitive tasks."
  ],
